<font color="#FF0000">WE WERE NEVER ALONE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep 27 21:55:23 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
There were always those times when the angels came.  Nothing could be explained any other way.  My grandfather a minister of 50 years and a major influence in my life ensured me that I would looked after.  A priest gave me a Saint Christopher's medal to wear.  I was never without it.<br><br>
There was always a higher presence, a protector.  If not I can't explain my existence today as I am sure you can't.  The books never talk of this, but they should.  When the nights were quite I could feel the closeness.<br><br>
When my best friend was killed I heard and felt something rush to me.  I knew instantly it was a last statement.  We are all connected somehow.<br><br>
My time in the artic after the war brought me closer to this.  I have to go now, time to think and not write.<br><br>
Thanks for reminding me, least I forget
<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


